@page "/"

<PageTitle>YouTube Catalog</PageTitle>

<div class="home-container">
    <h1>Welcome to YouTube Catalog</h1>
    <p class="lead">Discover the top trending videos from your favorite YouTube channels</p>

    <section class="features">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Multi-Channel Search</strong> - Enter multiple YouTube channels and fetch the top videos across all of them
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Customizable Results</strong> - Choose how many videos to display (top X) and the time period (past Y days)
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Fast Results</strong> - Results are cached to provide quick responses for repeated queries
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Channel Discovery</strong> - Search for channels by name to easily find and add them
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="getting-started">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to the <NavLink href="catalog">Catalog page</NavLink></li>
            <li>Add your favorite YouTube channels (by ID or URL, or search by name)</li>
            <li>Set how many videos you want to see and the time period</li>
            <li>Click "Fetch Results" to see the top videos</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="about">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>
            The YouTube Catalog application fetches video metadata from your selected channels, 
            filters them by publication date, sorts by view count, and displays the results in an easy-to-browse format.
        </p>
        <p>
            Results are cached to improve performance, and you can fetch updated results at any time.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>

